  "text": "To begin with, the absolute AoA values differ strongly among the models. For the first three decades of the simulations 10 (i.e. the mean from ) the values range between 5.52 years in the MRI model and 3.18 years in the ACCESS model simulation. This topic had already been discussed for example in SPARC (2010) and in [CITATION_1] . Analysing the hindcast simulations of the CCMVal-2 and the CCMI-1 projects, [CITATION_2] showed that it is mainly the mixing rather than the residual circulation that causes the large AoA spread and that this is likely linked to the different resolutions of the model simulations.",
